    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-07T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-07T20:00:00-05:00" n="270"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d270">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 103.96/126b</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-07T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 7, 1917, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5982. For <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_MVC1">McCormick</persName> for
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_TAE1">Taylor</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_CB1">Colby</persName> from War Trade Board:</p>
                <p>Our 18. We suggest in order to get the ships moving that you propose that all
                    Dutch steamers whether empty or loaded be allowed to make two round voyages to
                    West Indies or one to South America or Pacific during the progress of these
                    negotiations, rates to be those of our Shipping Board Chartering Committee.
                    Propose the same to Sweden understanding that some of those now in Pacific Ocean
                    would need to be allotted to carry grain from Australia.</p>
                <p>Above after conference with <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_CSR1"
                        >Crawford</persName>, <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_PLE1"
                        >Percy</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
